    "caption": "Gentle giant of the rainforest — and fiercely loyal to his family.",
    "shortDescription": "Gorillas live in close family troops and spend their days eating, playing, and grooming. When a silverback male needs to make a point, he stands up tall and beats his chest with cupped hands — the boom travels through the forest like a drum. Despite the theatrics, gorillas are patient, peaceful plant-eaters most of the time. Fun fact: Gorillas share about ninety-eight percent of their DNA with humans, which shows up in everything from their expressions to the way they hold their babies."
